   {:e #blake3 "e45a1ec3112ec1a058c926f169250f23345b55b789dd5f106b86bdf5fcefab82" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "OPERATIONAL ALIGNMENT GAP: DDIS says agents should follow a 10-step cycle (orient, associate, assemble, plan, execute, observe, harvest, seed, reflect, handoff). Agents naturally do 3 (plan, execute, monitor). The other 7 are ceremony. COTX-5 (universal observe) eliminated structuring ceremony. The active observer eliminates observation ceremony. The optimal end state: agents never think about element types. Everything is an observation. The coherence engine classifies observations into policy-defined categories based on attribute patterns. INV/ADR/NEG are post-hoc labels applied by the engine, not pre-hoc categories the agent must choose.; BEDROCK SYNTHESIS: Braid is infrastructure for organizational learning. One atomic operation at every level: observe reality, compare to model, reduce discrepancy. Eight divergence types enumerate all ways models fail. Three learning loops (weight calibration, structure discovery, ontology discovery) close the system completely. Calibrated policies transfer via CRDT merge. The bootstrap starts convergence; the loops find the optimum. The system does science on itself. This insight was discovered through the self-bootstrap: the system participated in discovering its own nature using its own mechanisms.; CONVERGENCE THESIS: All six review problems (F(S) dishonesty, task overload, footer noise, performance, zombie specs, shallow witnesses) share one root cause: every loop in the system is open. Observations dont feed back into fitness. Executions dont feed back into task closure. Guidance doesnt respond to changes. The fix is architectural: close all loops via the policy manifest + active observer + calibration loop. OBSERVER-4 (calibration) is P0 because it IS the reason the policy manifest exists. Without calibration, the manifest is a static guess. With calibration, it is a learning system.; Session entity: :task/t-66ba9d3e; Session entity: :recon/trace-1d4026a59d12580f; Session entity: :recon/trace-78a4d7abefd2c692; BEDROCK: Braid is infrastructure for organizational learning. The atomic operation at every level of the system is the same: observe reality, compare to model, reduce the discrepancy. Datom assertion, boundary evaluation, gradient routing, weight calibration, structure discovery, and ontology discovery are all instances of this one operation at different levels of abstraction. The 8-type divergence taxonomy is a complete enumeration of the ways a model can diverge from reality. If you detect and reduce all 8, the model converges toward truth. The product is not a tool for software coherence. It is infrastructure for the progressive, empirical, closed-loop reduction of divergence between what an organization believes and what is actually true about its domain.; TRANSFERABLE EPISTEMOLOGY: Calibrated policies are transferable knowledge. A team that ran braid for 100 sessions has an empirically discovered model of what coherence means in their domain. New teams start from that calibrated policy instead of the generic bootstrap. CRDT merge applies to policies: two teams that independently learned about the same domain can merge their coherence models via set union of policy datoms. This is how organizational knowledge scales — not through documentation or training but through merging empirically calibrated coherence models. The same merge operation that combines datom stores combines what organizations have learned about what matters.; Session entity: :recon/trace-dc7c84d8aef82d37; Session entity: :recon/trace-dc9f417bb76ba499; Session entity: :recon/trace-623b584db153cf85; THE FINAL LOOP: Ontology discovery. The calibration loop learns weights. Boundary discovery learns structure. But neither learns the ontology — what categories of knowledge exist. The missing loop: cluster observations by attribute patterns, detect recurring structures that dont match any declared claim type, propose new categories. Example: 12 observations all reference file paths with confidence over 0.8 and led to task creation — thats implementation insights, a category the policy doesnt have. The system proposes: I detected a recurring pattern. Should I create a new claim type? This closes the ontology loop: policy defines categories, usage reveals new categories, policy evolves. The systems theory of knowledge becomes more complete through use. All three loops closed: weight calibration (OBSERVER-4), structure discovery (OBSERVER-5), ontology discovery (OBSERVER-6).; Session entity: :task/t-9d954382; TRANSFERABLE EPISTEMOLOGY: Calibrated policies encode empirical discoveries about a domain. CRDT merge on policies means two teams that independently learned about coherence in their domain can combine their learning through set union. Cross-domain merge reveals universal coherence patterns. The accumulation of calibrated policies across domains converges on a domain-general theory of coherence: the universal structure of how knowledge should be organized, verified, and maintained. Discovered from measurement, not from philosophy.\nSession entity: :task/t-5375c27a; Session entity: :task/t-730e1b5f" :op :assert}
